Good food good prices
this is my fav food to order duhh

I go to this excellent place from time to time because I love the ambiance that is characterizes this restaurant. The team is awfuly cordial and qualified. The service is awfully fast. Needless to say, the food they serve is highly distinguished. I came many times and I was always joyful. The payment is honest. I recommend this restaurant to all my friends.
The guy running this place should let someone else answer the phone, he is rude, if you order something that he doesn't have, he just hangs up like :/ what is wrong with you?   This isn't China.

Good standard American-Chinese food - has all your favorites and the sauces and seasonings are not too sweet/sticky/overwhelming as some places. Good, quick service. Never had a bad thing off the menu. Fast delivery. Lunch portions are huge lately.
The service is not good
Super rude. Their "fried rice" is just rice with soy sauce poured on top. I asked for an extra bag and they refused. Acted like I was asking for a free entire meal.

We used to live 2 blocks from it and ordered regularly. Best egg rolls,  vegetable fried rice,  moo shoo, OMG the best. We live in Indiana  and have my niece  bring out enough food for three days of eating . We wa t Choi to open up a place here because they don't know  how to cook out here.
The broccoli with garlic sauce is nice and spicy. Huge portions, good prices, the kindest family. Go-to classic spot.

Called to place an order for delivery, and I think he stated that he didn't have what I wanted and hung up on me instead of asking me if I might be interested in something else. Tried calling back and never answered the call!
Delicious and quick service!!

Service was terrible kid was rude with attitude taking our order father n kid were more into playing cards than good customer service the food wasn't good either orange chicken had no flavor king bao beef was ok rice tasted old dry egg rolls
Horrible first hangs up on me for trying to order a lunch special past the lunch time. Second time I call says he won’t deliver horrible service.
It says they close at 11PM, I called for delivery  at 9:30PM and they said they were closing.
Went in for lunch, the guy at the counter coughed into his hands, smoked a cigarette visibly in the kitchen and then proceeded to stick his whole hand INSIDE of his pants. I’ve lost my appetite.
I've had bad fried rice, then I had Choi's.

Was very fresh & yummy. Ordered orange chicken for my picky husband,  and he liked it, not too spicy. I had beef with mixed vegetables,  but ordered beef & green beans which they were out of, and I didn't mind the change because it was my 2nd choice. I was happy with what I got. Tasted good & fresh. Also ordered crab rangoon which my husband wasn't too crazy about because it was too creamy & had onions which he doesn't like. All the food was good and plentiful for the price. It's hard to find good Chinese food since our favorite place closed over 20 years ago, but after a long search I think we found a replacement restaurant finally. And my cousin owns a Chinese restaurant, but I'd prefer Choi's food now. Ssshhhh, don't tell them.
This place is solid Chinese. I’ve ordered at least 30 times from them over 7 years and this place just kills it each time.
Low quality food and rude customer service
Deliveries are always prompt and the food is always hot and fresh. Outstanding service.
My boy always got the hook up when I’m hungry

This place is one of my favorite restaurants! It’s hard to find decent Chinese in Chicago but this location is always clean and their quality of food has been consistent. I would eat there every Sunday for a year straight and I never got tired of their food! Their service was great, there food was delicious and I always received a large portion. I can’t speak for their take out service  but I always enjoy dining in Choi’s restaurant. Their food is flavorsome and comforting; I enjoy their clean minimalist atmosphere. I believe this restaurant is authentic and affordable, that’s why I will always support this restaurant.
Love there egg rolls would travel just to get them and there orange chicken the best fried crispy pieces with great sauce😋
Food is better than the place looks.  Better if its fresh, delivery makes cruchy things soggy.
One of my friends work here anyways thought it would just just be cool to leave this here
This place is great. I eat here or take out almost every week!
Beautiful little family-owned restaurant
We loved the space and the food. The owner and his family were around chatting in a relaxed way. It was nice. Calm. And we  enjoyed the food. Prices very good too.
Hood food .good price..enough said
This restaurant wouldn’t even serve me I cam in and they said no more.... it literally had to because of my race That’s the only thing I could even think of

Ordered takeout from here a few times now and always had consistent service and tasty food. There are a few tables, should you want to eat in, but I have yet to do so. The chicken and broccoli is just that - not overloaded with onions like some other establishments, but simple with a brown sauce that adds flavor.  Potstickers come with gyoza sauce, not that red vinegar stuff. Portions are great and price is reasonable. Looking forward to exploring the menu and finding new favorites.
Good food.
Very good food been eating here for over 3 years
Very fast delivery. Food is good.
Been eating here since I moved to Chicago 6 years ago. Best orange chicken in the city that I’ve tried at a very fair price.
Very good food every day
Have had delivery, carry out, and eaten at the restaurant. What you get for the price is exceptional. Crab Rangoon is honestly amazing.

Chicken with broccoli lunch special. Be chicken fried rice was pretty good the chicken was broccoli headed next to the flavor and I normally don't eat egg rolls but the lunch portions are kind of small so I ate the egg roll and it was probably one of the best egg rolls I've had

The worst service! Three years ago I walked into Choi's and an Asian male (who also appears to be the restaurant owner/partner) is masogynistic, rude and disrespectful!!! When I was placing my order I had a question about a certain dish since I suffer of some food allergies and the Asian male Yelled /Lashed out at me verbally in front of other patrons. He felt he was in authority to verbally mistreat me. I stopped the order and the mistreatment by walking out! That was three years ago AND I NEVER STEPPED FOOT INTO THIS ESTABLISHMENT AND I NEVER WILL!

First visit. Went in to get steamed rice for my sick dog. Was tempted by the menu. Got the orange chicken which was about as perfect as it gets.  Citrusy without being sweet. A little chile heat but not overpowering.  Will definitely go back. Looking forward to trying their smoothies, too.
Big portions
Guy is rude at the counter and food wasnt fresh

Hello, I've been living here since 1994. This place is great, ignore everyone complaining about poor service just because the new kids in town are NOT I repeat are NOT used to other humans groveling at their feet.
Nasty food...
the owner very nice and the place has good prices.

This guy that is always there is a huge jerk, I just got turned away for asking if the egg rolls had red meat and took the menu off my hands. Might be senile, might be drunk. . . Not sure. . . I strongly suggest skipping this place  cause he is a huge rude jerk.
I personally think that this is the best place to eat in Logan Sqare!  The shrimp fried is amazing.  I just don't know a place better than this!
Great food, fast service and lots to choose from!! 😃
Favorite restaurant in Logan Square.  The Sesame Chicken and Mongolian beef are stupendous!  Especially recommend the lunch deals.  You will leave a happy camper with a big ol' belly of joy.

Poor service was to be expected because of the previous reviews. My food was undercooked (practically raw) and the rice was over cooked. All in all, a very horrible experience. Additionally, their son was working at the front counter. He might have been 12 at the most. Aren’t there child labor laws in place?
Great food, cranky guy, the food is what counts!!
Food was fast, fresh, and delicious. Large portions.

Yes, the owner is gruff and speaks limited English. Honestly, who cares? We're all adults, we don't need or want everywhere to be a flippin' Chili's.  It took me 2 years to try Choi's, even though I live around the corner. It just doesn't look like much.  The portions are huge, the food quality is very high, and the prices are low. It won't win any awards for complexity, but if you want to pay $15 for enough tasty standard Chinese fare to last you 2 days, this place is fantastic. Big soft pot-stickers and crispy Crab Rangoon, great curry, kung pao and cashew chicken. Dishes are full of veggies and nuts. Hit's the spot. Definitely order takeout or delivery because the ambiance is non-existant.
Pretty solid Chinese food! Nothing mind blowing but it's a reasonably priced Chinese take out place, also has limited dine in space.

An old Logan Square stronghold... Food is subpar, service is subpar... The owner is almost ALWAYS agitated... Not sure if he isn't happy with how his life has gone or just doesn't like the area but something bothers him everyday. The food is overly greasy and I only come here if Van Phat down the street is closed.
The food their was amazing to the point where i couldn't believe it! I shall come back in the Future to expierience it again.

Bad customer service , I brought combination fried rice for two and they give me 1 plate I asked nicely for extra plate and the guy who was on front got mad and said share the 1 and told him again polite pls can I have extra plate , finally agree to give me the other plate but with bad attitude and the rice was old by the way

Been ordering here faithfully for a couple years now. I ordered orange chicken for delivery, the delivery guy comes, which im such a "regular" he says "hi my friend" ect, well i got sweet and sour chicken instead of the orange chicken. So i call assuming it wouldnt be a problem since i considered myself a "regular" but no, the guy argues with me over the phone about what i ordered! Who does that? Ive never once complained. So i talked to my "friend" the delivery driver, who agreed with the guy who answered the phone but yet says he'd bring me my orange chicken......2 hrs ago. Smh. Needless to say i didnt get my order and unfortunately they lost my business. Worst customer service ever.
The service was bad, food was mediocre and the place smelled like rancid oil.

This place is horrible. Even do the guy to, he have a horrible Actitud. And the food it is no good too. The place is in bad conditions to. A don't like this place,  and can even recommend you this place. Just tried to take a look to the kitchen, the guy don't let you see inside. But you right Michelle Garcia.  the customer service is horrible to.

It was my first coming into this place. I simply asked if they had shrimp egg roll. The owner, clear gave me a dirty look and said no no and waved his handed at me to leave. I said wow u don't have to be rude. He said no no sell here..never will..i just walk out. I will never come here.
Incredibly rude guy at the counter. He seemed annoyed to have to take my order.  General tso's chicken was inedible, completely undercooked. Won't be going back after this experience.
Good food but terrible service and rude. It depends who answer the phone. Not consistent.
Been a loyal customer for 10 years now..I moved to suburbs and still come all the way to Logan Square for them. Great service, friendship and excellent clean food..they are the best!
Great family run restaurant. The shrimp fried rice is to die for

I recently ordered egg drop soup for takeout, and when I went to eat it later that day realized that there were enormous chunks of green mold in the soup. Typically my food is good, but I will not be returning in the future.
Not terrible, not great. Pot stickers have thick, spongy, greasy skins, and were mostly flavorless. Orange chicken needed A LOT more sauce. Crab Rangoon, though, was delicious.
Insane quantity of food and very good quality, very central location. No complaints.
The staff was rude. The food was inadequate.
Cheap and sizeable portions, decent food, I am Chinese and eat there regularly. Try the beef chow fun...
Love this place, always a good experience. Food is great never a bad complaint
Been coming here for a long time. I moved to Alban Park for a while and still came back for Choi' s. Nothing fancy just basic comfort food for a decent price.
Totally recommended! The food arrived quick and warm to me. The wonton soup is good and the crab rangoon are nicely filled and creamy. I love it. Good price, lots of food.
Favorite local spot. Affordable and HUGE delicious dish portions!! Love this place.

Standard Chinese-takeout fare done right. As others have mentioned, the food is delicious and you get very generous positions. If you can order during the lunch special you'll get more than you paid for.

This place is beautiful. Their food makes me wanna cry when I eat it because it's so good. The owner is rude sometimes, but I get it, having worked with customer service and having to deal with Logan square types. I wouldn't have come back if the food weren't so damn good. It's worth the abuse and the guy is actually really great once you understand him. That fakes customer butt kissing is never genuine anyway.
I frequent Choi's for a delicious meal that is priced affordably for lunch and dinner. They are super fast to cook your food and you're out the door.
Some of the best potstickers I've found.

I been ordering from here for years and the food is great! Delivery is always super fast and the delivery guy is always polite and nice. Owner's not the warmest but has never been rude or derespectful to me. Jumbo shrimp fried rice, curry chicken, fried crabmeat, and shrimp with lobster sauce are definitely some of my favs.
He's nice too me. And the food is delicious so I go or order often.
The fried rice tastes like cigarettes. So if you like eating out of an ashtray this is your place. Fed it to my cats.
Yea the guy is always in a grumpy mood but so what the food is delicious! I love eating there or as take out!
Good food!
Naw..just naw. This isn't even good for cheap Chinese food ( which i can usually dig) massive portions don't make up for greasy dishes with rubbery, cheap meat. Not even drunk.
Delicious!
Absolutely love the food here. I grew up on this food! No other restaurant can compare to the food here trust me I tried.

CLOSED ON TUESDAYS! I don't know why, but I always want Choi's on Tuesdays– and unlike Yelp, Google keeps telling me it's open. Either way, this place is exactly what you want when you think Chinese take-out. Fried rice is perfect, crab rangoon is plentiful, and the Hunan beef is beautifully spicy.
I love coming to Chois I always get the edamame. The staff and owner are friendly and remember  their regulars. :)
Perfect for a lazy night in. The servings are huge and everyone there is very nice.
Excellent service, quick and delicious. Has great flavor and the owner is very nice. My favorite is the orange chicken here not too sweet but just right with a zing.
